## Core Principles
- Feature synergy: All features work together for maximum power
- Complexity adaptation: Orchestration adapts to task complexity
- Pattern learning: Learned patterns become reusable components
- Self-orchestration: System orchestrates its own feature usage
- Parallel execution: Subagents enable parallel pattern discovery
- Cascading enrichment: Rules trigger rules for exponential context

## Do Not
- Use features in isolation (always orchestrate together)
- Ignore complexity when selecting orchestration patterns
- Skip pattern library consultation for Level 3+ tasks
- Launch subagents sequentially (always parallel when possible)
- Ignore file context (globs always inform orchestration)
- Treat Cursor memories as authoritative
